speech.p: I am grateful for the hon. Gentleman's question. I know the premium that he places on communication and language skills, as do I. I will investigate the question that he raises about guidance for the Department of Health and write to him. I can tell him, however, that speech and language therapists are increasingly working in and through children's centres, which I am very pleased about. We will also develop a programme called Let's Talk to help people to develop children's vocabulary, because we know that that makes a big difference to a child's ability to communicate.

On outreach, we have also funded two additional workers in every children's centre, to ensure that we reach those families who would perhaps not necessarily find it that easy to come of their own volition. Going out to those families can encourage them to come into the children's centres.
